[2] Missouri
Date: Fri 15 May 2020 5:16 PM CDT
Source: KY3 [edited]
https://www.ky3.com/content/news/Taney-County-Health-Dept-confirms-three-cases-of-Hepatitis-A-570516341.html


The Taney County Health Department has identified 3 cases of hepatitis A. Hepatitis A is a viral infection that affects the liver. Infection may occur by eating contaminated food or drink, in addition to person-to-person contact. Taney County health officials say none of these cases were related to food establishments or restaurants.

Hepatitis A symptoms include fatigue, fever, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, dark urine, light stools, and yellowing of skins and eyes.

Nationally, the hepatitis A outbreak has affected people since March 2017.

